      "acceptanceCriteria": "Commercial CFD solver with documented QA procedures and version control meets MRL 2 requirement of Gradation 1.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 used under institutional software QA policy. Version-controlled simulation scripts archived in institutional repository. Solver release notes reviewed for relevant bug fixes. MRL 2 requires only basic QA documentation, which is satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver passes standard benchmark verification cases (lid-driven cavity, pipe flow) at Gradation 1.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent has been independently verified against standard CFD benchmarks including the Taylor-Green vortex and Poiseuille flow. Published verification documentation from the vendor and independent literature confirm Gradation 1 code verification is satisfied for the incompressible Navier-Stokes solver used here."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) for hemolysis index QoI must be less than 5% on the medium-to-fine mesh refinement pair.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed: coarse (4.2M cells), medium (8.7M cells), fine (17.1M cells). Richardson extrapolation applied. GCI for relative hemolysis index = 1.8% (medium-fine pair), satisfying the < 5% criterion. Asymptotic range confirmed with GCI ratio = 1.02. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions replicated in simulation within ±5% for flow rate and rotational speed across all 5 operating points.",
      "rationale": "FDA benchmark experimental data for the generic centrifugal blood pump used. All 5 flow-speed combinations (2–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM) reproduced in CFD boundary conditions within ±2.1% of reported experimental values. Blood viscosity modeled using Carreau-Yasuda non-Newtonian model with parameters matched to experimental fluid properties. Gradation 2 met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted relative hemolysis index RH within ±15% of experimental measurements at all 5 operating points; pressure rise within ±10%.",
      "rationale": "CFD-predicted RH values compared against experimental hemolysis measurements from FDA benchmark study. Maximum deviation across 5 operating points: 11.3% for RH, 7.8% for pressure rise. All predictions within acceptance bands. Worst-case operating point correctly identified as 2 L/min / 3500 RPM in both experiment and simulation. Gradation 2 achieved."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs used in validation (RH index, pressure rise) are the same quantities used in the clinical decision (tolerance sensitivity analysis).",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index is both the primary validation QoI and the primary decision QoI for the tolerance sensitivity analysis. Pressure-flow characteristic is a secondary QoI used to confirm hydraulic fidelity. Direct correspondence between validation and decision QoIs confirmed. No surrogate QoIs required. Gradation 2 satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
